content:
Create a Live Connection to Snowflake

To create live connections to Snowflake, enable CRM Analytics Direct Data for external data sources and Explore External Data Directly. Connect to Snowflake with OAuth (Beta).

Configure Snowflake, Salesforce, CRM Analytics, and an external OAuth authorization server like Okta. Add the live Snowflake connection in CRM Analytics.

Create the Live Connection

In CRM Analytics, click Data Manager > Connect tab > Connect to Data > Live Connections. Click Add Connection > Snowflake Direct Connector and enter its settings.

Create Live Datasets for a Snowflake Source Table

After creating the live connection, create a live dataset that lets users explore Snowflake tables or views available with the connection.

Snowflake Live Connections Settings

* Connection Name: Identifies the live connection
* Developer Name: API name for the connection (unique and alphanumeric)
* Description: Internal description of the connection
* Authentication Type: UserBasedOAuth or Password
	+ Named Credential: OAuth credential field
	+ Username and Password: Password authentication fields
* Schema: Snowflake schema to explore with the connection
* Role: Snowflake role assigned to the user
* Warehouse: Snowflake warehouse name
* Username: Snowflake username to connect to the schema
* Account: Name of your Snowflake account
title: Create Live Connection to Snowflake
